<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,538,504,530]" box="[189,538,504,530]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,538,504,530]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,538,504,530]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Morphological observations</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,550,647]" box="[234,607,550,576]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,607,550,576]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Light microscopy (
<figureCitation box="[468,599,550,576]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 78-99</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,550,647]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Frustules in girdle view rectangular, clearly bent around the transapical axis and with clearly recurved apices (
<figureCitation box="[279,412,621,647]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 78-80</figureCitation>
). Valves linear to narrowly linear-lanceolate with almost parallel to slightly convex
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835058" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3835058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835058/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" startId="8.[189,241,1860,1886]" targetBox="[189,1399,724,1818]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1860,2028]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,332,1860,1886]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 54-77.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Van de Vijver. Light" authorityName="Van de Vijver. Light" box="[347,884,1860,1887]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Achnanthidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="lailae">
<emphasis box="[347,526,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Achnanthidium</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[541,608,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">lailae</emphasis>
Van de Vijver. Light
</taxonomicName>
and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Clearwater Mesa (James Ross Island). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,881,1895,1921]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">54-56</emphasis>
. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,257,1931,1957]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">57-64</emphasis>
. LM views of raphe valves. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[600,669,1931,1957]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">65-74</emphasis>
. LM views of rapheless valves. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1055,1084,1931,1957]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">75</emphasis>
. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[457,486,1966,1992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">76</emphasis>
. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1062,1091,1966,1992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">77</emphasis>
. SEM external (right) and internal (left) view of an entire raphe valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,267,646]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
margins and clearly protracted, rostrate to even capitate apices (
<figureCitation box="[941,1073,267,293]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 81-99</figureCitation>
). Valve dimensions (n=25): length 9.5–18.0 µm, width 
<quantity box="[517,658,303,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="1.9">1.9–3.1 µm</quantity>
. Raphe valve (
<figureCitation box="[838,969,302,329]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 81-91</figureCitation>
) concave with a very narrow linear axial area, almost not discernible near the valve apices. Central area elliptical to rounded, very small, almost indistinct, formed by 2–3 more widely spaced striae. Central striae often lacking extending the central area up to the valve margin. Raphe straight, filiform with simple, straight proximal raphe endings. Distal raphe hardly discernible in LM. Striae weakly radiate near the valve center, becoming parallel and even convergent near the apices, well visible in LM, ca. 
<quantity box="[837,895,478,505]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.128" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="32.0">32 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[901,978,479,505]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, more densely spaced near the valve ends. Rapheless valve (
<figureCitation box="[467,598,514,540]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 92-99</figureCitation>
) slightly convex with narrow, linear axial area, widening to form a weakly elliptically, never transapically elongated central area. Fascia never present. Central 2–3 striae more distantly spaced. Striae weakly radiate throughout, becoming more parallel to even convergent near the apices, ca. 
<quantity box="[419,478,619,646]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.89" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="35.0">35 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[485,565,619,646]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" startId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" targetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1860,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,341,1860,1886]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 78-103.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light" authorityName="Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light" box="[349,1235,1860,1886]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Achnanthidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="sieminskae">
<emphasis box="[349,665,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Achnanthidium sieminskae</emphasis>
Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light
</taxonomicName>
and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[867,935,1895,1921]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">78-80</emphasis>
. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[259,327,1930,1956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">81-91</emphasis>
. LM views of raphe valves. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[664,732,1930,1956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">92-99</emphasis>
. LM views of rapheless valves. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1113,1157,1930,1956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">100</emphasis>
. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[477,521,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">101</emphasis>
. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1050,1094,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">102</emphasis>
. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[456,500,2001,2027]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">103</emphasis>
. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,267,721]" box="[234,792,267,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,792,267,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Scanning electron microscopy (
<figureCitation box="[623,783,267,293]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs 100-103</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,267,721]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Valve face of the raphe valve clearly concave. Valve face/mantle margin forming a weakly raised hyaline border separating valve face striae from mantle areolae. Striae, ca. 
<quantity box="[1075,1179,338,364]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.382" metricValueMax="8.636" metricValueMin="8.128" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="in" value="33.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="32.0">32–34 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[1187,1266,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, composed of 2–3 small, rounded areolae (
<figureCitation box="[567,669,374,400]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
) followed near the valve center by a thin, slit-like, marginal areola (
<figureCitation box="[279,385,409,436]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
). Near the apices, striae more dense, ca. 
<quantity box="[883,946,409,436]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="in" value="40.0">40 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[955,1037,410,436]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, composed of only 3 rounded areolae. Mantle areolae slit-like (
<figureCitation box="[582,751,445,471]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs 100, 102</figureCitation>
). Raphe almost straight with simple, straight proximal raphe endings (
<figureCitation box="[375,481,481,507]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
). Distal raphe fissures weakly deflected, continuing slightly beyond the last striae terminating on the valve face/mantle junction. Internally, proximal raphe endings shortly bent into opposite directions(
<figureCitation box="[479,579,552,578]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
). Distal raphe endings terminating in small helictoglossae (
<figureCitation box="[1281,1385,552,578]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
). Internal areolae openings covered by hymenes (
<figureCitation box="[756,860,588,614]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
). Striae of the rapheless valve almost equally spaced throughout the entire valve, 
<quantity box="[629,736,623,649]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.89" metricValueMax="9.144" metricValueMin="8.636" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="in" value="35.0" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="34.0">34–36 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[748,831,624,650]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, composed of 2–5 rounded areolae sometimes terminating in one slit-like areola (
<figureCitation box="[594,697,659,685]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 102</figureCitation>
). Mantle areolae slit-like. Internal areolae openings covered by hymenes (
<figureCitation box="[346,449,695,721]" captionStart="Figs 78-103" captionStartId="9.[189,241,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,720,1819]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 78-103. Achnanthidium sieminskae Witkowski, Kulikovskiy &amp; Riaux-Gobin. Light and scanning electron micrographs of a population on Iles Kerguelen. 78-80. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 81-91. LM views of raphe valves. 92-99. LM views of rapheless valves. 100. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 101. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 102. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 103. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835060/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
